name: Zixuan Song
headline: Software Engineer at Amazon
creator: False
bio:
Explorer, innovator, and first principles thinker. I am a Software Engineer with 3+ years of experience at Amazon. I have led teams of engineers and delivered robust and scalable solutions that power the day-to-day operations of airlines within our aviation vertical. I am a self-motivator, a fast learner, an effective communicator, and a team player. My motto is: Don’t just work smart, work smart and hard.  

During my professional career, I have always followed these two core tenets that have helped me succeed:
1. Unrelenting pursuit of truth: From learning a new software framework to tackling an elusive bug, one must dispel the notion of magic. Every system, no matter how large or complex, can be unraveled to its source. Only when we rigorously interrogate the truth do we gain concrete understandings and valuable insights.
2. Uncompromising integrity: Instead of taking shortcuts, I put forth my utmost effort in delivering solutions. When confronted with imperfections, I embrace criticism and strive to do better. I am continuously seeking opportunities for improvement. And when they are identified, I eagerly work with my team to integrate them into our product.

My passion for creating software extends beyond my current role. I have additional interests in reverse engineering, high performance computing, and embedded systems. I am always open to new opportunities in the role of a software engineer, where I can leverage my experience and values to drive impactful solutions.

name: Sumeet Deshpande
headline: Software Development Engineer 2 at Amazon | Ex-PlayStation, Oracle
creator: False
bio:
I am currently working as a Software Development Engineer 2 at Amazon in the Amazon FinTech Org. I hold a Master's Degree in Software Engineering from San Jose State University (SJSU). While pursuing my Master's, I interned at PlayStation as a Software Engineer where I worked on automating & improving the release process of PlayStation's internal Telemetry packages.
 
Prior to this, I worked at Oracle as an Applications Developer 1 for the Document Management System (DMS) module of Oracle Banking Platform (OBP), a premium banking product catering to the world’s top-tier banks. I steered the module's frontend & backend development activities for incorporating multiple new features & was also the contingent Single Point of Contact (SPoC) of the module.

TECHNICAL SKILLS:

Programming Languages: Java, JavaScript, TypeScript 
Frameworks: Apache Kafka, Express, Oracle ADF, Spring MVC, Java Swing, J2EE
Web Development: React, Redux, NodeJS, REST API, Bootstrap, HTML, CSS, GraphQL, JWT, Handlebars templating language 
Databases: MySQL, MongoDB 
Others: Amazon AWS, Git, SVN, BitBucket, Eclipse, VSCode, Oracle JDeveloper, Oracle Weblogic, Android, Hibernate, NPM

name: Nate Venckus
headline: Software Development Engineer II at Amazon
creator: False
bio:
I graduated from Purdue University in the Summer of 2020 with a B.S. in computer science. I began my career at Amazon in August of 2020, working as a Software Development Engineer on Amazon Pharmacy.

name: Ryan Ellison
headline: Software Development Engineer @ Amazon
creator: False
bio:
As a Data Platform Architect Intern at Cox Enterprises, I am developing and implementing data solutions using iPaaS technology. Additionally, I contributing to bring modern DevOps practices to Cox Enterprises. I also lead other interns to develop a minimum viable product as part of our intern boot camp.

I am pursuing a Bachelor of Science degree in computer science at Purdue University, with a dual specialization in machine learning and software engineering. My projects include creating a mobile app for marine biologists, an iOS app that implements machine learning for personalized suggestions, analyzing genomic data for Alzheimer's research, and building a web app for a local business. I am passionate about applying my skills and knowledge to solve real-world problems and to create positive impacts.

In addition to my academic and professional pursuits, I have also demonstrated leadership and entrepreneurship skills through various extracurricular activities. I was elected as a vice president for my fraternity, where I helped organize events and fundraisers, and fostered a culture of inclusivity and respect. I also cofounded a small business in high school, where I made and sold homemade pickles at local farmer markets, and managed costs and revenue. Through these experiences, I have learned to work with diverse teams, communicate effectively, and adapt to changing situations.

name: Wei Yi Tan
headline: SDE @ Amazon | Purdue CS
creator: False
bio:
I am a student at Purdue University with a major in Computer Science and a minor in Psychology. I am currently pursuing the security and machine intelligence tracks. I am fluent in Java, Python, and C, but also have some experience with SQL, Swift, C++, Assembly, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, Bash, and R. Additionally, I have worked with some frameworks and development platforms such as Google Cloud Platform, Flask, and Twilio. 

Currently, I am the initiative lead of the Computer Science Undergraduate Student Board (USB), where I advocate for international students in the computer science and data science community. During my time at USB, I have organized and hosted career events, such as USB’s first networking event and the first international student careers panel event. I am also a teaching assistant for CS 18000, a course on object-oriented programming, and have been a teaching assistant for two other courses in the past semesters.

bio:
My name is Ashwin Saxena and I’m graduate student studying Computer Vision a senior Computer at the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor. I completed my undergrad in Computer Science last year at UMich as well. My technical skills include proficiency in C++, Java and Python, as well as knowledge of DevOps, Agile, and ROS. Over the course of my education, I have developed an affinity for robotics and autonomous vehicle systems, and the limitless possibilities in that field. I am currently seeking a software engineering internship in a similar field.

This summer I worked at Amazon.com as a Software Development Engineering Intern in the AWS Sagemaker team, where I was responsible for developing a query engine in the form of a command line interface tool which queries and displays information about AWS region builds and helps in the automation process. During the academic year I’m the President for Autonomous Robotics Vehicles project team, where we build an autonomous robot to compete, and an elected senator of the Engineering Student Government. In my free time I enjoy baking, watching movies, and working out.

headline: SDE 2 @ Amazon | Illini | Ex. Sr-SWE@ Myntra
creator: False
bio:
I am pursuing my Master's degree in Computer Science at the University Of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign, focusing on natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Previously, I graduated from the College of Engineering, Guindy, with a Bachelor of Engineering in Computer Science. I have core competencies in React, Go, GraphQL, Node.js, and Android development.

Before joining UIUC, I worked as a Senior Software Engineer at Myntra, one of India's leading online fashion platforms. I was part of the team that developed and enhanced several features for the Myntra app, such as calling the delivery agent, multi-seller exchange, business continuity plan, disaster recovery, and international shipping. I also led the development of the in-app ticketing service for customer issues via the help center page. I contributed to the improvement of the user experience, security, and performance of the app, using my skills in React, Node.js, Go, and GraphQL. 

I am passionate about creating accessible and inclusive solutions for diverse users, and I won the Best Project Award for developing a prototype of a code editor that converts spoken natural language to C code. I value teamwork, innovation, and customer satisfaction, and I am eager to learn from and collaborate with other talented professionals in computer science.

name: Vedant Bajaj
headline: SWE @ Amazon | Ex- SWE @ PayPal | Computer Science & Business @ UMass Amherst
creator: False
past_company_2: Manning College of Information and Computer Sciences, UMass Amherst
bio:
Hello! I'm Vedant Bajaj, a recent graduate from the University of Massachusetts Amherst with a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science and a minor in Business. My academic journey has been marked by a deep engagement with cutting-edge fields such as Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Web Development, complemented by a strong foundation in Computer Vision, Database Management, and Operating Systems. This robust blend of coursework has not only honed my technical skills but also my strategic thinking, as evidenced by my GPA of 3.97/4.0 and consistent presence on the Dean’s List.

My passion for technology has translated into real-world impact through internships where I've developed solutions like a real-time KYC document verification system, contributing to a significant uptick in customer success metrics, and an employee management software that streamlined operations. My roles have varied from software engineering internships to contributing to the academic community at UMass as an Undergraduate Course Assistant in Artificial Intelligence and a Resident Assistant, where I supported and mentored over 300 residents.

Beyond my academic and professional pursuits, I find joy in photography, chess, and soccer—whether playing on the field or immersing myself in the strategic beauty of the game. These hobbies not only offer me a creative outlet but also keep me grounded and connected to my community.

I'm currently on the lookout for full-time opportunities where I can bring my blend of technical expertise, innovative thinking, and collaborative spirit to create meaningful technological solutions. Let's connect and explore how we can drive forward with impactful projects!
